    "Tables S1-S4 present the correlations of individual characteristics (attitudes toward AI, demographic information, patient status, healthcare-related profession or training) with the evaluations of the medical advice and the decision to save the link to the fictious tool.",
    "Correlations of behavior in study 2 (ratings of empathy, reliability, comprehensibility and willingness as well as the decision to save the link) and attitudes toward AI (use, impact, risk) for the \"AI\" condition.",
    "Test statistics are based on Pearsons's product moment correlation coefficient (two-sided testing, no adjustments for multiple comparisons were made).",
    "Higher values for \"AI risk\" indicate that AI is rather seen as an opportunity than a risk for healthcare.",
    "*** p < 0.001, ** p < 0.01, * p < 0.05."
